<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL COOLER AND FILTER - Oil
        Cooler - Leakage Test
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Leakage Test</title>
        <para>Inspect the oil cooler assembly for leaks by using the following air pressure test:</para>
        <figure id="f1200903" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2558.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Air Pressure Test</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler Front Header</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Test Plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler Filter Header</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the heater and block the heater plug.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil filter and all pipe plugs in the headers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the oil cooler test plate to the oil cooler.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the pressure gauge to test plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200904" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/eg2559.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Oil Pressure Check</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Test Plate</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler Filter Header</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Cooler Front Header</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure Gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform the oil pressure check as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Leave the water side 1/4 NPTF hole in the test plate open.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install an air pressure hose to the oil side of the 1/4 NPTF hole in the test plate.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Immerse the assembly in a container of clean water.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply 276 - 414 kPa (40 - 60 psi) of air pressure while the assembly is immersed.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Inspect the header castings, O-rings and water side 1/4 NPTF hole for moving or growing
                    bubbles. Replace components as required.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Perform the water side oil cooler check as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Leave the oil side 1/4 NPTF hole in the test plate open.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install an air pressure hose to the water side of 1/4 NPTF hole in the test plate.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Immerse the assembly in a container of clean water.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply 276 - 414 kPa (40 - 60 psi) air pressure while the assembly is immersed.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Inspect the header castings, O-rings and oil side 1/4 NPTF hole for moving or growing
                    bubbles. Replace components as required.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
